You’re now hitting the last real blocker before install starts 👍
This error is very common in agent-based installs.


---

🚨 PROBLEM BREAKDOWN

❌ Error 1:

Host couldn't synchronize with any NTP server

❌ Error 2:

No connectivity to the majority of hosts in the cluster


---

🧠 WHAT THIS MEANS (Simple)

Issue	Meaning

NTP error	Node time is wrong / unsynced
Connectivity error	Nodes cannot reach each other (network problem)


👉 Both must be fixed, otherwise install WILL NOT start


---

🔥 FIX 1 — NTP (MANDATORY)

✔ Check current time on all nodes

Run on each node:

timedatectl

👉 If you see:

NTP synchronized: no ❌ → problem confirmed



---

✅ Fix using Chrony (BEST METHOD)

Step 1 — Edit config

sudo vi /etc/chrony.conf

Add your local DNS server (recommended):

server 72.2.0.34 iburst

👉 Or public (if internet works):

server 0.pool.ntp.org iburst


---

Step 2 — Restart

systemctl restart chronyd


---

Step 3 — Verify

chronyc sources -v

👉 You should see ^* → synced


---

Step 4 — Force sync (if needed)

chronyc makestep


---

🔥 FIX 2 — HOST CONNECTIVITY (CRITICAL)

This is your main issue now.


---

✔ Test from each node

From bscmaster1:

ping 72.2.0.15
ping 72.2.0.17

From bscmaster2:

ping 72.2.0.13
ping 72.2.0.17


---

❌ If ping fails → root cause


---

🔍 MOST COMMON CAUSES

1. 🚨 MTU ISSUE (VERY LIKELY in your case)

You configured:

mtu: 8500

👉 This is dangerous unless FULL infra supports jumbo frames


---

✅ FIX (RECOMMENDED)

Change in agent-config.yaml:

mtu: 1500

👉 Then regenerate ISO


---

2. 🚨 Firewall blocking

On all nodes:

systemctl stop firewalld
systemctl disable firewalld


---

3. 🚨 Wrong subnet / routing

Check:

ip route

👉 Must have:

default via 72.2.0.1 dev ens1f0


---

4. 🚨 Switch / VLAN issue

Ensure all nodes are in same VLAN

No L3 restriction



---

🔥 QUICK DEBUG COMMANDS

Run on each node:

ping -c 3 72.2.0.13
ping -c 3 72.2.0.15
ping -c 3 72.2.0.17

nc -zv 72.2.0.13 22


---

🚀 FASTEST WAY TO FIX EVERYTHING

✔ Do this:

1. Set MTU → 1500


2. Disable firewall


3. Fix NTP


4. Reboot nodes




---

🔥 EXPECTED RESULT AFTER FIX

You should see:

Host is ready to install

instead of:

insufficient


---

💡 IMPORTANT INSIGHT

👉 OpenShift requires:

All nodes reachable (L2/L3)

Time difference < 4 minutes


Even small issues → install blocked


---

🚀 NEXT STEP

After fixes, run again:

openshift-install agent wait-for bootstrap-complete --log-level debug


